                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10044/162.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Leishman says outlying garrisons are surrendering rapidly and that it looks
                    as though occupation of all points would be complete by night, including Yildiz.
                    Says no action taken regarding Sultan, nor has anything definite been decided
                    concerning cabinet, and that a state of siege has been proclaimed in
                    Constantinople and surrounding districts. Mr. Leishman says the able manner in
                    which the entire military movement has been conducted so far furnishes good
                    ground for belief that proper order will be maintained in the capital.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
